supports him.

2041
01:57:37.644 --> 01:57:41.424
Don't get me wrong, we love our son dearly and

2042
01:57:41.504 --> 01:57:44.084
very happily care and support him

2043
01:57:45.803 --> 01:57:49.584
now to the extent that we're able to and for how long

2044
01:57:50.004 --> 01:57:50.784
we're able to.

2045
01:57:51.844 --> 01:57:52.264
But

2046
01:57:53.744 --> 01:57:57.533
it takes so much love, strength, and

2047
01:57:57.704 --> 01:58:01.354
patience. You can't take that for granted, and you can't

2048
01:58:01.384 --> 01:58:03.064
prescribe this through legislation.

2049
01:58:03.544 --> 01:58:07.524
Families need strengthening, so they can do this as much as they can.

2050
01:58:08.204 --> 01:58:12.184
You can't use this as an excuse to reduce

2051
01:58:12.204 --> 01:58:14.804
supports. And I think forcing

2052
01:58:15.824 --> 01:58:17.064
families to support

2053
01:58:18.044 --> 01:58:21.574
a disabled person against their will and beyond their

2054
01:58:21.644 --> 01:58:22.384
capacity

2055
01:58:24.204 --> 01:58:26.304
would just lead to resentment,

2056
01:58:27.404 --> 01:58:31.364
family members burning out even more than they currently do, family

2057
01:58:31.373 --> 01:58:34.264
relationships breaking down, and I think

2058
01:58:35.504 --> 01:58:39.304
all of this can also put disabled people then at great risk

2059
01:58:39.404 --> 01:58:42.424
of being neglected and abused in their own homes

2060
01:58:43.424 --> 01:58:44.484
behind closed doors.

2061
01:58:46.644 --> 01:58:50.444
So that's my first concern. The second concern is about the possibility of means

2062
01:58:50.524 --> 01:58:54.424
testing. As a family, we face the same

2063
01:58:54.464 --> 01:58:56.204
financial pressures as everyone else,

2064
01:58:57.004 --> 01:58:59.824
but our ability to earn an income is

2065
01:59:01.964 --> 01:59:05.104
much more compromised than it would otherwise be because of our care

2066
01:59:05.164 --> 01:59:09.084
responsibilities for Moritz. Example of my

2067
01:59:09.124 --> 01:59:12.444
wife, she basically had to completely abandon her career.

2068
01:59:12.544 --> 01:59:12.684
Mm.

2069
01:59:12.924 --> 01:59:14.944
She was unable to work for eight years.

2070
01:59:15.304 --> 01:59:17.264
Now she's working very limited hours

2071
01:59:18.504 --> 01:59:22.484
at a pay rate that is a fraction of what she used to earn

2072
01:59:22.844 --> 01:59:24.044
because the primary

2073
01:59:25.424 --> 01:59:29.124
task that we have is raising our son and his brother.

2074
01:59:29.224 --> 01:59:32.904
And equally, my own

2075
01:59:32.964 --> 01:59:36.764
career, I can only do jobs that allow me the time,

2076
01:59:37.044 --> 01:59:40.784
energy, and flexibility to also support our

2077
01:59:40.804 --> 01:59:41.984
son. So

2078
01:59:43.424 --> 01:59:46.124
that's compromising our ability to earn income.

2079
01:59:46.184 --> 01:59:46.984
On top of that,

2080
01:59:48.124 --> 01:59:51.804
we are faced with the reality that our son will not be-- Once he is an adult,

2081
01:59:52.024 --> 01:59:55.784
he will not be able to have his own job and earn his own living,

2082
01:59:56.364 --> 01:59:59.924
so we need to consider his needs and our

2083
01:59:59.984 --> 02:00:03.824
needs in our future planning, our financial planning,

2084
02:00:04.244 --> 02:00:07.604
our retirement, and so we're trying to save

2085
02:00:08.324 --> 02:00:08.664
a bit

2086
02:00:09.684 --> 02:00:13.364
for our and his future. And so if the government was to turn around and

2087
02:00:13.444 --> 02:00:17.384
say, "Now you need to use up your funds first before we come

2088
02:00:17.424 --> 02:00:17.744
back,"

2089
02:00:18.924 --> 02:00:22.464
we would basically be left with nothing for our retirement, nothing

2090
02:00:22.504 --> 02:00:25.924
for his future. And I think means testing DSS

2091
02:00:26.024 --> 02:00:29.544
supports would simply condemn disabled people and their

2092
02:00:29.564 --> 02:00:33.464
families to lifelong poverty and with no hope of working our

2093
02:00:33.504 --> 02:00:37.304
way out of this situation. Because the thing with disability is

2094
02:00:37.704 --> 02:00:41.504
it could happen to anyone. Our son didn't choose to be disabled, but he

2095
02:00:41.564 --> 02:00:43.394
is really stuck with this disability.

2096
02:00:43.404 --> 02:00:47.254
It's permanent and his support needs, as significant as they are, they're also

2097
02:00:47.284 --> 02:00:51.244
permanent. It's not like he can just do some training, find a

2098
02:00:51.304 --> 02:00:54.203
job, and then sort of work his way out of this situation.

2099
02:00:54.884 --> 02:00:58.664
And so because of this, and this is really a long game, and

2100
02:00:58.684 --> 02:01:02.524
we're very limited in our ability to adapt

2101
02:01:02.604 --> 02:01:03.504
to changes.

2102
02:01:05.004 --> 02:01:08.904
So what disabled people and families really need is

2103
02:01:09.384 --> 02:01:12.904
long-term certainty that the government will not

2104
02:01:12.984 --> 02:01:16.004
withdraw their supports and be there for them.

2105
02:01:16.424 --> 02:01:16.884
Thank you.

2106
02:01:16.904 --> 02:01:17.054
Thank you.

2107
02:01:17.054 --> 02:01:18.404
Thank you, Christian, for making a submission this morning.

2108
02:01:18.414 --> 02:01:19.304
No, thank you very much.

2109
02:01:19.844 --> 02:01:20.704
Thank you very much.

2110
02:01:22.844 --> 02:01:26.124
Our next speaker is Kate. Also in person, Kate.

2111
02:01:29.384 --> 02:01:29.664
Okay.

2112
02:01:31.244 --> 02:01:34.704
Okay, we'll move to Daniel. Daniel Flay.

2113
02:01:42.260 --> 02:01:44.260
Mr Chair, I'm followed by my daughter and my wife.

2114
02:01:44.420 --> 02:01:45.760
Oh, great. Welcome back.

2115
02:01:45.769 --> 02:01:46.400
We'll set up together.

2116
02:01:55.560 --> 02:01:56.340
Good day.

2117
02:01:58.139 --> 02:01:58.820
Good morning. Welcome.

2118
02:01:59.400 --> 02:01:59.660
Morning.

2119
02:01:59.780 --> 02:02:00.980
How are you?

2120
02:02:05.920 --> 02:02:05.950
I'm good.

2121
02:02:05.950 --> 02:02:07.120
Do you want another chair or...

2122
02:02:08.040 --> 02:02:10.040
No.

2123
02:02:12.980 --> 02:02:13.920
While we're setting up-

2124
02:02:15.620 --> 02:02:15.800
Hey

2125
02:02:15.940 --> 02:02:17.120
... my submission.

2126
02:02:18.620 --> 02:02:21.060
For those who are new here, so that was here for Cerebral Palsy Society.

2127
02:02:21.380 --> 02:02:25.120
But I'm here in my personal capacity as a father of a 13-year-old daughter with

2128
02:02:25.160 --> 02:02:26.810
cerebral palsy, Indy.

2129
02:02:27.800 --> 02:02:31.440
My daughter's disability affects almost every aspect of our daily lives.

2130
02:02:31.480 --> 02:02:33.540
We've organized our lives around her support needs.

2131
02:02:33.580 --> 02:02:37.520
My wife, Amy, has given up her career to support our daughter and coordinate

2132
02:02:37.540 --> 02:02:41.520
her care. Together, we provide over 100 hours of unpaid support every

2133
02:02:41.600 --> 02:02:41.840
week.

2134
02:02:42.960 --> 02:02:46.659
Government funding sits atop an enormous foundation of unpaid care.

2135
02:02:47.500 --> 02:02:49.680
This already saves the government significant costs.

2136
02:02:50.420 --> 02:02:54.000
The question is how much more government can reasonably expect families to absorb,

2137
02:02:54.400 --> 02:02:57.060
and how that impacts a disabled person's independence.

2138
02:02:57.640 --> 02:03:01.340
We provide all the unpaid care we do because we love our daughter, but we need

2139
02:03:01.440 --> 02:03:01.860
support,

2140
02:03:02.740 --> 02:03:04.860
and we can't be her caregiver forever.

2141
02:03:04.920 --> 02:03:08.200
How many teenagers and young adults do you know who spend every day with their

2142
02:03:08.240 --> 02:03:12.200
parents? We want our daughter to have the same independence, relationships, and

2143
02:03:12.260 --> 02:03:14.899
opportunities that any young person should expect.

2144
02:03:15.020 --> 02:03:16.560
She has a human right to be independent.

2145
02:03:17.010 --> 02:03:20.720
A system that relies increasingly on parents and family risks moving in the

2146
02:03:20.780 --> 02:03:24.560
opposite direction. There's been a suggestion that the bill won't change anything

2147
02:03:24.580 --> 02:03:27.680
and simply codifies the current system. That is not correct.

2148
02:03:28.040 --> 02:03:31.340
Under the current system, support is fundamentally based on need.

2149
02:03:31.850 --> 02:03:35.560
Person's disability-related needs are assessed first, and then the role of

2150
02:03:35.600 --> 02:03:37.600
natural support such as family is considered.

2151
02:03:37.980 --> 02:03:41.800
The current system asks, "What support does this person need and what help can

2152
02:03:41.920 --> 02:03:45.660
family reasonably provide?" The bill changes that starting point.

2153
02:03:45.720 --> 02:03:49.240
It states that families have a responsibility, quote, "In the first instance

2154
02:03:49.860 --> 02:03:52.899
for providing support." This is a significant shift.

2155
02:03:52.959 --> 02:03:56.700
It moves families from being partners with government to being the primary

2156
02:03:56.740 --> 02:03:59.560
source of support before government support is considered.

2157
02:04:00.140 --> 02:04:04.020
That inevitably raises questions about the capacity and resources of family

2158
02:04:04.100 --> 02:04:07.400
members rather than focusing first on the needs of the disabled

2159
02:04:07.460 --> 02:04:11.310
person. The reality is that families, including ours,

2160
02:04:11.360 --> 02:04:14.860
are already contributing at or beyond sustainable levels.

2161
02:04:15.270 --> 02:04:16.080
There is no more.

2162
02:04:16.880 --> 02:04:20.240
Support will not magically transfer to family members simply because

2163
02:04:20.320 --> 02:04:21.780
legislation assumes it can.

2164
02:04:22.600 --> 02:04:24.600
There are also wider consequences.

2165
02:04:25.100 --> 02:04:28.960
Disability support does not just support the disabled people, it enables

2166
02:04:28.980 --> 02:04:32.140
their families to participate and contribute to society.

2167
02:04:32.300 --> 02:04:36.140
This brings me to means testing. It's been suggested that means testing already

2168
02:04:36.160 --> 02:04:39.680
exists, and the bill does not change this. That is not quite correct.

2169
02:04:39.800 --> 02:04:43.560
Some limited forms of means testing do exist, but they only apply in

2170
02:04:43.700 --> 02:04:47.040
very specific circumstances, namely housing and vehicle

2171
02:04:47.100 --> 02:04:50.920
modifications for adults. The bill enables means testing to be

2172
02:04:50.940 --> 02:04:54.000
applied across all disability support programs.

2173
02:04:54.580 --> 02:04:58.110
If means testing is to remain in the bill, it should be limited to housing and

2174
02:04:58.200 --> 02:04:59.940
vehicle modifications for adults.

2175
02:05:00.720 --> 02:05:04.700
Access to disability support should be determined by need, not by family income

2176
02:05:04.760 --> 02:05:08.580
or assets. Access to health or education services is not means

2177
02:05:08.640 --> 02:05:10.940
tested. Why should disability support be?

2178
02:05:11.820 --> 02:05:15.340
If means testing is introduced, families will face a

2179
02:05:15.360 --> 02:05:19.200
difficult choice. In my case, if I have to choose between remaining in paid

2180
02:05:19.260 --> 02:05:23.060
employment while spending my disposable income on disability supports,

2181
02:05:23.480 --> 02:05:27.080
or leaving the workforce to become my daughter's caregiver, I would likely leave

2182
02:05:27.120 --> 02:05:30.940
the workforce. But that would not be good for my family, my community

2183
02:05:30.980 --> 02:05:34.730
through my work for iwi, and charitable organizations, the economy,

2184
02:05:35.280 --> 02:05:39.270
or importantly, my daughter. The result would be a highly educated and

2185
02:05:39.300 --> 02:05:42.900
experienced professional would leave the workforce to perform work that government

2186
02:05:42.960 --> 02:05:46.779
previously supported. This is not an efficient use of

2187
02:05:46.840 --> 02:05:48.620
skills or good for national productivity.

2188
02:05:49.260 --> 02:05:52.870
Earning an income has also enabled us to spend tens of thousands of dollars on

2189
02:05:52.940 --> 02:05:54.580
disability equipment and other costs.

2190
02:05:55.800 --> 02:05:59.499
To conclude, disability support is not a wealthy benefit.

2191
02:05:59.540 --> 02:06:03.460
It's an investment that enables disabled people and their families to

2192
02:06:03.499 --> 02:06:05.760
participate, contribute, and thrive.

2193
02:06:06.460 --> 02:06:10.410
I ask that disability support remains based on need and that

2194
02:06:10.420 --> 02:06:14.090
government continues to meet its responsibility to support disabled

2195
02:06:14.180 --> 02:06:18.160
people and their whanau to participate fully in society. Kia ora.

2196
02:06:18.670 --> 02:06:20.920
Kia ora. Thanks, Daniel. Warren question.

2197
02:06:21.620 --> 02:06:24.060
Thank you. Thanks for coming back, Daniel.

2198
02:06:25.160 --> 02:06:28.920
I take your point, we've heard it many times about the need to clarify the

2199
02:06:28.960 --> 02:06:32.780
means testing. I can refer you to the minister's first reading

2200
02:06:32.860 --> 02:06:35.600
speech on this bill, where she laid it out quite clearly.

2201
02:06:36.140 --> 02:06:38.540
But I wonder if you,

2202
02:06:39.640 --> 02:06:43.400
as part of your submission, are suggesting that we actually tighten

2203
02:06:43.640 --> 02:06:47.500
up the wording in there so it does clarify what it's used for, because it's

2204
02:06:47.620 --> 02:06:48.000
used for

2205
02:06:48.820 --> 02:06:52.020
vehicles and spectacles if they're needed.

2206
02:06:52.090 --> 02:06:55.900
And so those things are assessed already, and

2207
02:06:55.940 --> 02:06:58.300
that's what the bill is designed to do.

2208
02:06:58.380 --> 02:07:01.020
But it's clearly got quite confused.

2209
02:07:01.080 --> 02:07:01.160
Yeah.

2210
02:07:01.260 --> 02:07:02.330
Would you be happy with that clarification?

2211
02:07:02.380 --> 02:07:04.970
Well, if the premise is we're not changing anything-

2212
02:07:05.300 --> 02:07:05.530
Yes, it is

2213
02:07:05.540 --> 02:07:06.800
... that needs to be clear in the bill.

2214
02:07:06.840 --> 02:07:06.850
Yes.

2215
02:07:06.880 --> 02:07:10.490
Because it's broad sweeping, and it gives the minister broad powers to

2216
02:07:10.520 --> 02:07:13.380
introduce means testing to all levels of disability support.

2217
02:07:13.430 --> 02:07:13.430
Yeah. And that's not-

2218
02:07:13.460 --> 02:07:14.940
So I would support that.

2219
02:07:15.040 --> 02:07:15.280
Okay.

2220
02:07:15.300 --> 02:07:19.000
And that, I think, is what's causing concern for the

2221
02:07:19.060 --> 02:07:20.020
disability community.

2222
02:07:20.030 --> 02:07:20.230
Yes. Yeah.

2223
02:07:20.260 --> 02:07:22.760
You've been here a couple of days. You'll hear more submissions.

2224
02:07:23.400 --> 02:07:27.280
I'm sure you've got many submissions in writing as well that are raising these

2225
02:07:27.320 --> 02:07:31.040
concerns. And it's the same with the family. Some people call it family first.

2226
02:07:31.100 --> 02:07:32.480
I call it family substitution.

2227
02:07:32.520 --> 02:07:32.660
Yeah.

2228
02:07:33.000 --> 02:07:36.540
But the first point is that families are at their capacity now.

2229
02:07:37.360 --> 02:07:40.280
So if it's to reflect the current system, that's more about partnership-

2230
02:07:40.640 --> 02:07:40.840
Yes

2231
02:07:40.900 --> 02:07:44.380
... and disability needs first, and then how can family support-

2232
02:07:44.460 --> 02:07:46.620
And the minister did address that in her first reading speech.

2233
02:07:46.680 --> 02:07:47.400
But clearly-

2234
02:07:47.460 --> 02:07:47.480
Yes

2235
02:07:47.490 --> 02:07:49.010
... their wording in the leg needs a tightening up.

2236
02:07:49.280 --> 02:07:52.960
Well, right. Unless you go to court, and I'm a former practicing lawyer,

2237
02:07:53.440 --> 02:07:54.080
you don't look at

2238
02:07:55.180 --> 02:07:56.540
first speech readings.

2239
02:07:56.880 --> 02:08:00.840
But that's actually used in clarification if there

2240
02:08:00.860 --> 02:08:02.190
are any legal tests to be made.

2241
02:08:02.340 --> 02:08:05.700
Yes. But my submission is something like law now.

2242
02:08:06.240 --> 02:08:09.460
It should be in the legislation, and that would deal with a lot of concerns,

2243
02:08:09.480 --> 02:08:11.200
particularly on means testing.

2244
02:08:11.800 --> 02:08:14.140
Thanks, Daniel. We'll now move to India Rose.

2245
02:08:14.260 --> 02:08:16.019
We look forward to hearing from you, India Rose.

2246
02:08:16.850 --> 02:08:16.850
Okay.

2247
02:08:17.380 --> 02:08:18.000
Welcome.

2248
02:08:21.872 --> 02:08:25.572
Hello. My name is India Rose. I'm 13

2249
02:08:25.632 --> 02:08:29.292
years old. I am here to speak up for

2250
02:08:29.372 --> 02:08:33.352
myself and other people with disabilities.

2251
02:08:33.972 --> 02:08:37.252
My biggest concern is that

2252
02:08:38.292 --> 02:08:42.172
this bill is written to protect the

2253
02:08:42.232 --> 02:08:46.172
government and not the disability

2254
02:08:46.292 --> 02:08:47.312
community.

2255
02:08:48.172 --> 02:08:51.832
So I worry that the government doesn't care

2256
02:08:51.912 --> 02:08:53.392
about us at all.

2257
02:08:54.322 --> 02:08:57.852
It seems like they only think about what's good

2258
02:08:58.672 --> 02:09:02.352
for them instead of actually helping us.

2259
02:09:03.832 --> 02:09:07.692
The government doesn't understand because they don't have a

2260
02:09:07.732 --> 02:09:11.492
disability, so why are they writing this without

2261
02:09:11.732 --> 02:09:11.992
us?

2262
02:09:12.092 --> 02:09:12.912
Hang on, darl.

2263
02:09:12.972 --> 02:09:16.632
This bill is literally setting us

2264
02:09:16.772 --> 02:09:19.482
up for failure in the future,

2265
02:09:20.312 --> 02:09:24.152
forcing us to be dependent on our families is

2266
02:09:24.232 --> 02:09:25.992
just disabling.

2267
02:09:28.592 --> 02:09:32.322
It's going to make it impossible for-- to

2268
02:09:32.432 --> 02:09:34.762
live our lives normally.

2269
02:09:36.172 --> 02:09:40.152
You have a responsibility to protect

2270
02:09:40.212 --> 02:09:43.292
disabled people, but what are you doing?

2271
02:09:43.792 --> 02:09:47.512
The answer is just making it

2272
02:09:47.752 --> 02:09:48.452
worse.

2273
02:09:48.672 --> 02:09:48.892
Mm.

2274
02:09:49.452 --> 02:09:50.352
It's getting--

2275
02:09:51.312 --> 02:09:55.212
It's making it darker and darker for us and

2276
02:09:55.292 --> 02:09:58.912
for me. I'm starting to get left in the dark,

2277
02:09:59.432 --> 02:10:03.332
which means it's hard for me to trust in anything now.

2278
02:10:04.562 --> 02:10:04.562
Mm.

2279
02:10:04.592 --> 02:10:07.792
Please change the bill so the government

2280
02:10:08.592 --> 02:10:11.572
and families are partners.

2281
02:10:12.392 --> 02:10:15.552
This will protect my rights.

2282
02:10:16.752 --> 02:10:17.972
I want a bill

2283
02:10:18.772 --> 02:10:21.772
that gives me a life where I can be

2284
02:10:21.932 --> 02:10:25.872
independent, uh, so I can do normal

2285
02:10:25.952 --> 02:10:29.752
things like going out with friends.

2286
02:10:31.412 --> 02:10:31.572
Yeah.

2287
02:10:31.952 --> 02:10:35.712
If able people have a way to do that,

2288
02:10:35.832 --> 02:10:39.792
then I should too. I need my support

2289
02:10:39.832 --> 02:10:43.612
workers, and that's why it needs to be protected

2290
02:10:44.992 --> 02:10:46.152
by the government.

2291
02:10:46.972 --> 02:10:50.762
Give us the chance to rebuild this disability

2292
02:10:51.252 --> 02:10:51.712
world

2293
